MEDIUM UNNECESSARY_CLONING: Unnecessary cloning of cryptographic keys, nonces, or data buffers in ext/crypto/decrypt.rs and related files can lead to performance degradation, increased memory usage, and reduced throughput when processing large amounts of data.

Impact:
- Increased memory allocation and copying
- Higher garbage collection pressure
- Reduced cryptographic throughput
- Poor performance in bulk data encryption/decryption scenarios

Fix:
1. Use references instead of cloning when ownership is not required:
```rust
